      <title>Desert Spirituality for City Folks - Part 17 - Anger</title>
      <link>http://feeds.ancientfaith.com/~r/SimplyOrthodox/~3/xvyq3DDVMcg/desert_spirituality_for_city_folks_part_17_anger</link>
     <guid isPermaLink="false">http://ancientfaith.com/podcasts/nassif/desert_spirituality_for_city_folks_part_17_anger#1728</guid>
 <description>At its core, anger is a dark and cruel wish for harm to come upon the person who hurt you.  The Desert Fathers had at least three strategies for conquering anger: 1) don't be surprised when anger enters your soul, 2) deal with it quickly, and 3) die to your ego.  A humorous story taken from the life of St. Makarios of Egypt illumines the way to an anger-free life.&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;
